1
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:07,560
Let's go over what we found.

2
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:11,200
I just checked with the local precinct.

3
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,240
701 and 801 did have a dispute.

4
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:18,280
They even called the cops over noise complaints.

5
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:20,400
What about you?

6
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:24,960
The old couple downstairs...

7
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:26,760
their only daughter died.

8
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:30,000
They say the upstairs neighbors killed her.

9
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,520
Someone actually died?

10
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,160
That serious?

11
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:38,600
That's what the old man told me.

12
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,800
Yiyi

13
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,520
Go check on her, quick

14
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,440
Yiyi

15
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,400
Yiyi

16
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,280
Yiyi

17
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,400
Open the door

18
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:19,920
Li Zifan

19
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,320
Behave yourself

20
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,480
The lady downstairs is calling the cops again

21
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,400
Kids forget things easily

22
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:30,240
He gets carried away when he plays

23
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:31,840
His dad's not home

24
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:35,080
I can't control him on my own

25
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:38,280
Why don't you just let the cops take him away?

26
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,040
You...

27
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:39,760
Look,

28
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,360
What kind of attitude is that?

29
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,480
Ma'am

30
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,160
I'm begging you, okay?

31
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:48,800
We have a family history of heart disease

32
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:51,760
We can't take him jumping like this every day

33
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,000
Young lady

34
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,960
Do you know how stressed grade schoolers are?

35
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:58,080
Out early, home late, every day

36
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,200
School

37
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:00,640
Tutoring

38
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,560
He only gets this little time to rest and play

39
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,840
And you won't even let him play?

40
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,400
What if my kid gets depression?

41
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,600
Bringing up your family medical history...

42
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,480
That's just bizarre

43
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,840
Why can't I play in my own home?

44
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:15,320
You...

45
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,120
Kid

46
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,840
It's not that you can't jump

47
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,760
But

48
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:23,320
You jump for so long after school every day

49
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:27,120
Grandpa and I both have heart problems

50
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:29,160
Your bad hearts mean you're weaklings

51
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:30,120
What's that got to do with me?

52
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,240
You...

53
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,360
How can you talk like that?

54
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:36,160
My dad says the weak get eliminated sooner or later

55
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,240
You're so weak, you should just die early

56
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,640
Stop wasting the country's resources

57
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:40,960
You...

58
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:43,120
Is that how your dad raised you?

59
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,080
Young lady

60
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:45,120
Calm down

61
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,360
There's no reasoning with his mom

62
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,880
Tomorrow we'll go find his dad

63
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:49,320
Okay

64
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:50,120
Don't be angry

65
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,840
Let's go, dear

66
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,640
We can't keep letting him act up like this

67
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,640
Don't be upset, okay?

68
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,040
Deep breaths, breathe, breathe

69
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,840
If you embarrass your dad at his company

70
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,040
You're gonna get a beating

71
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,360
Then one morning,

72
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:07,800
The old couple found their daughter was gone

73
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,680
When they found her again

74
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,720
She had collapsed outside unit 801

75
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,040
They say she died of a heart attack

76
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,240
Help!

77
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,280
What are you doing?

78
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:18,320
What's your deal?

79
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:19,840
Trying to pull a Staged accident?

80
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,280
Let me tell you, my family has no money.

81
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:24,120
Go pull a Staged accident somewhere else.

82
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,880
What a sight. Hand me my medicine.

83
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,800
No wonder that evil spirit

84
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,200
showed up at Lucky Realty that day.

85
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,480
You actually saw that thing?

86
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,200
Could the old couple be out for revenge,

87
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,640
deliberately haunting the house?

88
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:45,880
What evil spirit?

89
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,160
It's actually possible.

90
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,880
They use their daughter's death to scare people,

91
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,480
while telling us the truth,

92
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,320
to stop the house from being sold.

93
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,200
No way.

94
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:56,680
That old couple doesn't look

95
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,280
like such evil people.

96
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:01,160
Losing their daughter is heartbreaking enough.

97
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,120
Why would they exploit her like that?

98
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:02,800
What evil spirit?

99
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,600
What's going on?

100
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,680
Who's the evil spirit?

101
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,120
The human heart is unpredictable.

102
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,240
It takes but a single thought.

103
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,280
You can never be sure about these things.

104
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,600
Wait, what are you guys talking about?

105
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,960
Who's following who?

106
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:16,600
Who's playing tricks?

107
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,480
That girl?

108
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,000
I...

109
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,200
I have no idea what you guys

110
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:21,520
are talking about.

111
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,320
Watch closely.

112
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:25,840
I'm the ghost.

113
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,040
Scared yet?

114
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,160
No, no, no.

115
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,280
Don't be so harsh on Lin You.

116
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:39,280
He's new and still learning the ropes.

117
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,440
Right?

118
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:41,880
Lin You.

119
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,720
Lin You.

120
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,360
What's up?

121
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:46,800
Just say what's on your mind.

122
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:50,080
We've been through the trenches together.

123
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:50,800
Right?

124
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,880
I just feel like...

125
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,320
I feel really bad for that old couple.

126
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,200
Burying one's own child drove the old lady mad.

127
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,040
And the old man despises that family.

128
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,920
Not only did they cause his daughter's death,

129
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,520
they didn't even bother to apologize.

130
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,640
So what does he want?

131
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,680
Just keep causing a ruckus

132
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,960
so the upstairs unit can't be sold?

133
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,680
That's just treating the symptom, not the cause.

134
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,760
I think it's actually pretty simple.

135
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:23,520
That old man

136
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,120
is just to have that family

137
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,160
kowtow

138
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,080
to his daughter

139
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,040
and apologize.

140
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,200
I doubt it'll happen.

141
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,200
Look at that woman.

142
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,320
Does she look the slightest bit guilty?

143
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,760
If we hadn't stopped her,

144
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,600
she'd have eaten the old couple alive.

145
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:44,760
This house...

146
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,000
we might not even need to sell it.

147
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,120
Hey, Old Wang.

148
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,600
You're really just gonna sit this one out?

149
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,320
Let me tell you,

150
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,640
this big lug said

151
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,720
it's probably staged by someone.

152
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,680
But what I saw wasn't that simple.

153
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:06,760
What are you looking at?

154
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,440
You actually believe

155
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:11,920
she's a ghost?

156
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:14,560
Worst case, I'll go with you.

157
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,840
Although...

158
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,000
I won't be much help either.

159
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,080
My name is Chen Shuyao.

160
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,200
If you dare bully Liuliu again,

161
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,840
I'll deal with you in a different way.

162
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:31,840
In this world,

163
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,159
do ghosts really exist?

164
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:35,960
If you believe they do,

165
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:36,799
then they do.

166
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:37,919
If you don't,

167
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:38,919
then they don't.

168
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,840
That's Boss Wang's famous line.

169
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,240
Isn't that just a...

170
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,800
Isn't that just conning people?

171
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:46,840
Don't worry about it.

172
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,360
You just need to know one thing.

173
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,720
Lucky Realty

174
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,720
is a gold-standard name in the industry,

175
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,640
mainly because your Boss Wang

176
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,080
is the best.

177
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:00,320
You know him well?

178
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:02,520
Before I turned ten,

179
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:03,960
I grew up here.

180
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,720
This place wasn't a realty before.

181
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:07,840
It was a Ritual hall.

182
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:09,760
A Ritual hall?

183
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:10,720
Alright.

184
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:11,560
Got it.

185
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,240
Let's go.

186
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,120
Old Wang said

187
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,560
he's smoothed things over with the lady.

188
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,440
Got an extra three percent commission.

189
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,760
We still need to keep selling the house.

190
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,040
Three percent, huh?

191
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,080
What a profiteer.

192
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,240
Shuyao.

193
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,680
Old Wang said

194
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,560
you shouldn't get involved in Lucky Realty's business.

195
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,600
But Old Wang isn't around, is he?

196
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,800
And my sister's too busy to mind me now.

197
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:37,840
Besides,

198
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,320
I've still got the flash bombs.

199
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:40,200
It's fine.

200
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,200
Just let me go.

201
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,520
I'll take responsibility if anything happens.

202
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,040
Where are you going?

203
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,040
To exorcise an evil spirit.

204
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,280
No wonder

205
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,800
his Bazi is so strong

206
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,160
Get in there!

207
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:19,360
Stop rushing me

208
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,320
I'm buying gear

209
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,440
If you don't engage in team fights, when will you?

210
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:24,520
I'm busy, hold on

211
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:26,320
Spit it out

212
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,280
Just say it

213
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:40,760
You can really see evil spirits?

214
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,440
Believe it or not

215
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:47,440
You think there's something around you?

216
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,680
How could Lin You have evil spirits near him?

217
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,640
Didn't you say his Bazi is super strong?

218
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:55,720
It clashes with evil spirits

219
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:56,880
So evil spirits are afraid of him?

220
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,960
Wandering evil spirits definitely fear him.

221
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,480
But if he's Bound by fate

222
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:03,760
with karmic ties

223
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,520
then it's a whole different story
